unctions prosody may have: On the one hand, prosody is a signal to syntax, marking e.g. constituent boundaries. On the other hand, prosodic or intonational features convey meaning; the concept “intonational morpheme” (as e.g. an exponent of information structural notions like topic or focus) puts prosody and intonation squarely into the syntactic representation. The proposals collected in this book tackle the intricate relationship of syntax and prosody in the encoding of sentences. The contributions build their cases on the basis of solid empirical evidence, adducing data from experiments or from the careful analysis of natural speech. The volume thus represents a state of the art survey of research on the syntax-phonology interface.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Phonetics & Phonology.2bisacsh  aProsody.  asentence structure.  asyntax-phonology interface.1 aAnttila, Arto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButt, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBögel, Tina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarlson, Katy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDozat, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGalbraith, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeim, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInaba, Jiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJabeen, Farhat, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJamieson, E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKentner, Gerrit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKentner, 